# User Guide

## Creating Your First Stock Alert

This guide explains how to create a stock alert using the Smart Stock Alert System dashboard.

---

## Step 1

Sign in to your dashboard using your account credentials.

---

## Step 2

From the navigation menu, select **Inventory**.

---

## Step 3

Choose the product you want to monitor.

---

## Step 4

Click **Create Alert**.

---

## Step 5

Enter the minimum stock quantity.

Example:

```
20
```

When stock falls below 20 units, an alert will be triggered.

---

## Step 6

Enter the email address where notifications should be sent.

Example:

```
manager@example.com
```

---

## Step 7

Enable the alert by switching the **Active** option to **On**.

---

## Step 8

Click **Save**.

Your stock alert has now been created successfully.

---

## Editing an Alert

1. Open **Inventory**.
2. Select the product.
3. Click **Edit Alert**.
4. Update the stock threshold or email address.
5. Click **Save**.

---

## Disabling an Alert

1. Open the alert settings.
2. Turn **Active** to **Off**.
3. Save your changes.

The alert will remain in the system but will no longer send notifications.
